FOR THE GUESTS AS WELL.

00:32:07,726 --> 00:32:09,961
SO, AMY, WHO‐‐
WHO'S THE CUSTOMER?

00:32:09,961 --> 00:32:13,498
IS IT THE HOTEL OR THE PARENT?

00:32:13,498 --> 00:32:15,500
WE HAVE MULTIPLE‐‐
MULTIPLE CUSTOMERS.

00:32:15,500 --> 00:32:17,636
THE, UM, ON ONE END,
IT'S THE RETAIL.

00:32:17,636 --> 00:32:19,137
IT'S THE ACTUAL CONSUMER.

00:32:19,137 --> 00:32:21,506
SO IT'S THE GRANDPARENT
OR IT'S THE PARENT USING IT.

00:32:21,506 --> 00:32:24,943
BUT THEN IT'S ALSO‐‐WE CAN SELL
TO THE HOSPITALITY INDUSTRY.

00:32:24,943 --> 00:32:27,946
THEY CAN USE IT
AS A RETAIL OUTLET AS WELL,

00:32:27,946 --> 00:32:30,449
BECAUSE THEY CAN OFFER IT
TO THEIR GUESTS TO‐‐

00:32:30,449 --> 00:32:32,184
FOR PURCHASE.

00:32:32,184 --> 00:32:34,186
WE LAUNCHED OUR PRODUCT, UM,

00:32:34,186 --> 00:32:37,322
IT HIT THE SHELVES IN AUGUST
OF THIS PAST YEAR,

00:32:37,322 --> 00:32:38,990
AND WE LAUNCHED IN TARGET.

00:32:38,990 --> 00:32:40,992
WOW.

00:32:40,992 --> 00:32:43,395
I'M IMPRESSED.
AND THE NUMBER IS?

00:32:43,395 --> 00:32:48,066
AND THE NUMBER IS, UH,
WE'VE DONE $200,000 SO FAR.

00:32:48,066 --> 00:32:51,169
WE GOT INTO THE LARGEST
HOTEL DISTRIBUTOR IN THE WORLD.

00:32:51,169 --> 00:32:54,039
WE'RE SHIPPING MARRIOTT‐‐
HILTON...

00:32:54,039 --> 00:32:56,708
HILTON‐‐
BEST WESTERN, WYNDHAM,
ROYAL CARIBBEAN,

00:32:56,708 --> 00:32:58,343
CARNIVAL CRUISE LINE.

00:32:58,343 --> 00:33:00,979
WHAT ARE THE SALES
THROUGH ALL THOSE CHANNELS?

00:33:00,979 --> 00:33:04,249
WELL, THIS IS COLLECTIVELY.
IT'S UP TO $200,000.

00:33:04,249 --> 00:33:07,085
AND THAT WAS
THE INITIAL OPENING ORDER?
YES.

00:33:07,085 --> 00:33:09,120
DID ANYBODY REORDER?
YES.

00:33:09,120 --> 00:33:11,690
YEAH.
WE'RE GETTING REORDERS
ALL THE TIME.

00:33:11,690 --> 00:33:14,860
(Barbara)
ALL THE RIGHT ANSWERS.
YEAH. DO YOU HAVE
A PATENT ON THIS?

00:33:14,860 --> 00:33:16,862
(Allison) TWO.
(Amy) YES, WE HAVE
TWO U. S. PATENTS.

00:33:16,862 --> 00:33:19,264
YOU HAVE DISTRIBUTION.
YOU HAVE SALES.

00:33:19,264 --> 00:33:23,602
YOU HAVE A PATENT.
WHY DO YOU NEED ANY MONEY?
NOBODY KNOWS WE EXIST.
IT'S A BRAND‐NEW PRODUCT.

00:33:23,602 --> 00:33:26,037
WE JUST NEED
MORE PRODUCT AWARENESS.
AND THAT'S WHAT
OUR ACCOUNTS HAVE TOLD US.

00:33:26,037 --> 00:33:29,608
NOBODY IS GOING INTO
A STORE RIGHT NOW...
AND LOOKING FOR COVERPLAY.

00:33:29,608 --> 00:33:31,276
SAYING "I NEED A COVERPLAY.

00:33:31,276 --> 00:33:33,278
I NEED A SLIPCOVER
FOR A PLAY YARD."

00:33:33,278 --> 00:33:36,281
GIVE ME A REAL, TANGIBLE REASON
WHY YOU NEED $350,000

00:33:36,281 --> 00:33:38,617
FOR YOUR BUSINESS TODAY,
BESIDES MARKETING.

00:33:38,617 --> 00:33:41,152
HOW WILL YOU SPEND IT?
HOW WILL YOU‐‐
(Allison) HOW WILL‐‐

00:33:41,152 --> 00:33:43,755
BREAK DOWN THE $350,000
REALLY QUICK.
OPERATION‐‐OPERATIONAL COSTS.

00:33:43,755 --> 00:33:45,757
OPERATION MEANS SALARIES,
YOU'RE SAYING?

00:33:45,757 --> 00:33:48,226
IT MEANS SALARIES. IT MEANS‐‐
EMPLOYEES, SALES REPS.

00:33:48,226 --> 00:33:49,995
WARE‐‐WAREHOUSING.

00:33:49,995 --> 00:33:53,231
WHAT'S THE‐‐THE AGE GROUP
OF‐‐OF THE‐‐
ZERO TO 2.

00:33:53,231 --> 00:33:55,867
THAT'S THE CONCERN THAT I HAVE
FROM ME IN MY BUSINESS,

00:33:55,867 --> 00:33:58,436
BECAUSE WHAT I DO
IS TELEVISION ADVERTISING.

00:33:58,436 --> 00:34:01,773
I CAN'T AFFORD TO BUY
MASS‐MARKET TV TIME

00:34:01,773 --> 00:34:05,644
TO GO TO SOMEBODY THAT'S GOT
A ZERO TO 2 YEAR OLD...
BUT IT'S A‐‐

00:34:05,644 --> 00:34:08,747
BUT‐‐BUT‐‐BUT‐‐JUST‐‐
WHICH IS‐‐WHICH IS
TOO NICHE FOR ME,

00:34:08,747 --> 00:34:11,750
SO I'M GONNA SAY I'M OUT.
OKAY.

00:34:11,750 --> 00:34:13,752
THANK YOU.
THANK YOU.

00:34:13,752 --> 00:34:16,254
AMY, HOW MUCH CASH
DO YOU HAVE INTO IT?

00:34:16,254 --> 00:34:18,256
WE EACH ARE ABOUT, UH,
WHAT, $50,000?
YEAH.

00:34:18,256 --> 00:34:20,292
INTO IT.
EACH OF YOU PUT UP
$50,000?

00:34:20,292 --> 00:34:23,261
MM‐HMM.
HOW LONG AGO?

00:34:23,261 --> 00:34:25,263
(Allison) A YEAR AGO.
OKAY, SO A YEAR AGO,
LET'S SAY...

00:34:25,263 --> 00:34:27,432
(O'Leary)
IT WAS WORTH $100,000.
IT WAS WORTH $100,000.

00:34:27,432 --> 00:34:29,401
WITH NO SALES, NO NOTHING,
JUST T‐‐
AND THE PATENTS
WERE PENDING, TOO.

00:34:29,401 --> 00:34:31,136
JUST AN‐‐JUST AN IDEA.

00:34:31,136 --> 00:34:33,405
AND A YEAR LATER,
THERE'S $200,000 IN SALES.

00:34:33,405 --> 00:34:36,408
(O'Leary) YOU'RE OFFERING ME
15% OF YOUR COMPANY

00:34:36,408 --> 00:34:40,111
FOR $350,000.

00:34:40,111 --> 00:34:42,113
THAT MEANS
YOU WANT ME TO BELIEVE

00:34:42,113 --> 00:34:46,051
YOUR COMPANY
IS WORTH $2 1/2 MILLION.

00:34:46,051 --> 00:34:48,119
THAT'S A LOT OF PEEPEE
AND POOH POOH.

00:34:48,119 --> 00:34:50,488
WE'VE GOTTEN INTO TAR‐‐TARGET
DOESN'T TAKE UNBRANDED PRODUCTS.

00:34:50,488 --> 00:34:52,657
I GET IT, BUT, LADIES,
DON'T BE‐‐
BUT‐‐BUT‐‐HEAR‐‐HEAR‐‐

00:34:52,657 --> 00:34:56,728
HEAR ME OUT. HEAR ME OUT.
DON'T BE SAVAGES.
WE'RE THE SHARKS, NOT YOU GUYS.

00:34:56,728 --> 00:34:58,697
(both laugh)
THIS IS UNBELIEVABLE.

00:34:58,697 --> 00:35:02,067
IT'S NOT WORTH
WHAT YOU'RE ASKING.
(singsongy) OH, REALLY?

00:35:02,067 --> 00:35:04,135
BUT I'M LOOKING
AT THE TWO OF YOU,

00:35:04,135 --> 00:35:06,137
AND I'M THINKING
YOU GOT THAT SPUNK

00:35:06,137 --> 00:35:09,140
THAT'S GONNA DRIVE THIS TRAIN
RIGHT TO THE FINISH LINE.

00:35:09,140 --> 00:35:10,642
NOW HERE'S THE OFFER‐‐

00:35:10,642 --> 00:35:13,211
I'LL GIVE YOU THE $350,000
FOR 40% OF THE BUSINESS,

00:35:13,211 --> 00:35:16,481
AND THE 40% IS NONNEGOTIABLE,
ALL RIGHT?

00:35:16,481 --> 00:35:18,483
AND THE $350,000 IS TO BE USED

00:35:18,483 --> 00:35:21,152
ONLY FOR THE DEVELOPMENT
OF THE PRODUCT‐‐

00:35:21,152 --> 00:35:23,455
NOT FOR SALARIES,
NOT FOR LITTLE VACATIONS,

00:35:23,455 --> 00:35:26,291
NOT FOR SPECIAL PROMOTIONS.

00:35:26,291 --> 00:35:28,593
$350,000‐‐THE FULL AMOUNT
YOU'RE LOOKING FOR...

00:35:28,593 --> 00:35:30,829
MM‐HMM.
FOR 40% OF THE BUSINESS.

00:35:30,829 --> 00:35:34,032
THAT LEAVES
BOTH OF YOU IN CHARGE.

00:35:34,032 --> 00:35:36,501
OKAY.

00:35:36,501 --> 00:35:38,970
I'LL GIVE YOU $350,000,

00:35:38,970 --> 00:35:41,773
AND I WILL HAND IT TO YOU
TOWARDS THE MANUFACTURING

00:35:41,773 --> 00:35:43,875
ON YOUR ORDERS.

00:35:43,875 --> 00:35:46,444
AND THEN I WILL BE WILLING
TO FINANCE

00:35:46,444 --> 00:35:48,446
ALL THE OTHER MANUFACTURING
AND PRODUCTION

00:35:48,446 --> 00:35:50,482
FOR THE EXISTENCE
OF THE COMPANY.

00:35:50,482 --> 00:35:53,284
BUT THAT COMES
WITH A 65% OWNERSHIP.

00:35:55,620 --> 00:35:58,156
AMY, THERE'S TWO OFFERS
ON THE TABLE.

00:35:58,156 --> 00:36:01,926
BARBARA'S OFFER IS $350,000
FOR 40% OF THE BUSINESS.

00:36:01,926 --> 00:36:03,428
IT'S GOT
SOME PROBLEMATIC CONDITIONS

00:36:03,428 --> 00:36:05,463
ON HOW TO USE THE MONEY.

00:36:05,463 --> 00:36:11,336
DAYMOND'S OFFER IS $350,000
FOR 65% OF THE COMPANY.

00:36:11,336 --> 00:36:14,339
BUT MINE ROLLS OVER TO YOU
HAVING A STRATEGIC PARTNER

00:36:14,339 --> 00:36:16,374
WHO WILL FINANCE FOR THE REST.

00:36:16,374 --> 00:36:18,376
THAT MEANS YOU GET
MY WAREHOUSING, TRUCKING,

00:36:18,376 --> 00:36:21,079
BILLING, SHIPPING,
EVERYTHING.

00:36:21,079 --> 00:36:23,782
AMY, ALLISON, WHY DON'T
YOU GUYS GO IN THE HALL...

00:36:23,782 --> 00:36:26,117
OKAY, OKAY.
AND DISCUSS IT
AND THINK ABOUT IT?

00:36:26,117 --> 00:36:27,619
THAT WE'LL DO.
OKAY.

00:36:27,619 --> 00:36:30,588
THANK YOU.
WE JUST NEED PEN, PAPER,
CALCULATORS. (laughs)

00:36:30,588 --> 00:36:33,124
(Robert laughs)
THANK YOU.

00:36:33,124 --> 00:36:35,660
OH, GOD.

00:36:35,660 --> 00:36:38,029
ALLISON, WHAT ARE WE
GONNA DO?

00:36:38,029 --> 00:36:41,366
YOU DON'T‐‐YOU DON'T CARE
SO MUCH ABOUT THE CONTROL.
BARBARA‐‐

00:36:41,366 --> 00:36:44,669
THESE GIRLS ARE CAPABLE.
THEY'RE TOTALLY CA‐‐
BARBARA, YOU'RE BEING
TOO GENEROUS.

00:36:44,669 --> 00:36:47,205
YOU'RE BEING TOO GENEROUS.
YOU'RE BEING
WAY TOO GENEROUS.

00:36:47,205 --> 00:36:50,041
BARBARA, THIS IS MY BUSINESS.
LISTEN, THIS IS MY BUSINESS.

00:36:50,041 --> 00:36:53,044
I KNOW THIS BUSINESS,
AND I NEED CONTROL.
IT'S A PRETTY COOL PATENT.

00:36:53,044 --> 00:36:55,680
A VERY COOL PATENT.
IT'S A FANTASTIC PATENT.

00:36:55,680 --> 00:36:57,182
(Harrington) YEAH.

00:37:26,111 --> 00:37:29,247
(whispers)
TA‐TA‐TA‐TA‐TA.

00:37:29,247 --> 00:37:31,249
(Allison)
SORRY FOR THE DELAY.

00:37:31,249 --> 00:37:33,118
(laughs)

00:37:33,118 --> 00:37:35,453
WHAT DO YOU WANT TO DO?
HERE'S OUR THOUGHT.

00:37:35,453 --> 00:37:38,356
(Robert) OKAY.
WE DON'T WANT TO‐‐WE DON'T WANT
TO GIVE UP CONTROLLING INTEREST

00:37:38,356 --> 00:37:40,225
OF OUR COMPANY.

00:37:40,225 --> 00:37:42,894
I COULD ASK FOR 50%
AND SAY LET'S BE EVEN.

00:37:42,894 --> 00:37:47,031
I ASKED FOR ONLY 40%
OUT OF RESPECT FOR YOUR TALENT.

00:37:47,031 --> 00:37:50,235
I JUST WANT TO BRING MY 35 YEARS
OF SAVVY BUSINESS EXPERIENCE‐‐

00:37:50,235 --> 00:37:53,238
I TOOK 1,000 BUCKS AND TURNED IT
INTO $66 MILLION,

00:37:53,238 --> 00:37:54,739
WHICH WAS NO ACCIDENT‐‐

00:37:54,739 --> 00:37:57,475
AND BRING IT TO YOUR TABLE
TO HELP YOU.

00:37:57,475 --> 00:37:59,644
BUT WHEN YOU START TALKING
ABOUT EXPERIENCE,

00:37:59,644 --> 00:38:01,880
WE TALK A DIFFERENT LANGUAGE.

00:38:01,880 --> 00:38:04,282
SHE COULD RUN CIRCLES
AROUND ME

00:38:04,282 --> 00:38:08,386
IN ANY ASPECT OF REAL ESTATE.
WHICH HAS NOTHING TO DO
WITH THIS BUSINESS.

00:38:08,386 --> 00:38:11,589
WE ARE TALKING A DIFFERENT
UNDERSTANDING OF BUSINESS.
I'M WITH YOU, DAYMOND.

00:38:11,589 --> 00:38:13,958
WHAT IF YOU GOT
A LITTLE MORE CASH?

00:38:13,958 --> 00:38:16,461
IF YOU HAVE AN ISSUE
WITH THE 65%,

00:38:16,461 --> 00:38:20,665
WHAT IF I CAME IN WITH DAYMOND
AND GAVE YOU $450,000

00:38:20,665 --> 00:38:24,269
INSTEAD OF THE $350,000
FOR THE 65%?

00:38:24,269 --> 00:38:27,672
IT'S THE 65%
THAT BOTHERS US.

00:38:27,672 --> 00:38:31,042
(Robert) $500,000.

00:38:31,042 --> 00:38:34,012
TAKE THE MONEY,
YOU CRAZY CHICKENS.

00:38:34,012 --> 00:38:36,247
TAKE THE MONEY.

00:38:36,247 --> 00:38:39,551
ONE OF THE THINGS‐‐
I KNOW YOU WANT THE 40%.

00:38:39,551 --> 00:38:42,654
WOULD YOU BE WILLING
TO COME DOWN ON YOUR PERCENT

00:38:42,654 --> 00:38:46,324
AND TAKE PART OF THAT
AS OWNERSHIP IN THE PATENT?

00:38:46,324 --> 00:38:48,893
WHOA. HOLD IT A MINUTE.
THIS INCLUDES THE PATENT.

00:38:48,893 --> 00:38:51,095
THE PATENT'S
THE HEART OF THIS BUSINESS.

00:38:51,095 --> 00:38:54,132
I DIDN'T KNOW YOU HAD
PUT THAT TO THE SIDE.
AMY, THE PATENT WASN'T
PART OF THE COMPANY?

00:38:54,132 --> 00:38:56,100
NO, THE PATENT IS‐‐
THE PATENT IS SEPARATE.

00:38:56,100 --> 00:38:58,336
ALLISON OWNS THE PATENT.
THE PATENT IS‐‐

00:38:58,336 --> 00:39:00,905
WHY HAVE YOU WASTED
OUR TIME?

00:39:00,905 --> 00:39:04,008
MY‐‐MY OFFER IS RETRACTED.

00:39:04,008 --> 00:39:07,312
MINE, TOO.
YEAH, MY OFFER'S
OFF THE TABLE.

00:39:07,312 --> 00:39:09,480
♪♪

00:39:18,957 --> 00:39:22,227
<i>AMY AND ALLISON HAVE</i>
<i>TWO OFFERS ON THE TABLE,</i>

00:39:22,227 --> 00:39:25,864
<i>BUT A NEW WRINKLE</i>
<i>COULD JEOPARDIZE EVERYTHING.</i>

00:39:25,864 --> 00:39:28,867
THE PATENT WASN'T PART
OF THE COMPANY?
NO, THE PATENT IS‐‐

00:39:28,867 --> 00:39:31,936
THE PATENT IS SEPARATE.
ALLISON OWNS THE PATENT.
MY‐‐MY OFFER IS RETRACTED.

00:39:31,936 --> 00:39:34,606
MINE, TOO.
YEAH, MY OFFER'S
OFF THE TABLE.

00:39:37,008 --> 00:39:39,377
LADIES, PLEASE,
FOR THIS KIND OF MONEY,

00:39:39,377 --> 00:39:41,412
YOU HAVE TO VET THE PATENT
INTO THE COMPANY.

00:39:41,412 --> 00:39:43,648
WAIT. WHO OWNS THE PATENT?
ALLISON OWNS IT.

00:39:43,648 --> 00:39:45,850
100%?
NO, I OWN 60%.

00:39:45,850 --> 00:39:48,119
WHERE'S THE REST OF IT?
AMY OWNS A PORTION

00:39:48,119 --> 00:39:50,288
AND MY EX‐HUSBAND
OWNS A PORTION.

00:39:50,288 --> 00:39:51,756
OH, MY.

00:39:51,756 --> 00:39:54,525
YOU HAVE TO BRING THAT
INTO THE COMPANY.
RETRACTO!

00:39:54,525 --> 00:39:56,828
WE NEEDED TO KNOW THAT.
YEAH, BUT IT'S NOT
VERY DIFFICULT‐‐

00:39:56,828 --> 00:39:58,997
(Robert) ALLISON‐‐
RETRACT.

00:39:58,997 --> 00:40:01,900
BUT SINCE I OWN‐‐
THE FIRST FOUR WORDS OUT OF
YOUR MOUTH SHOULD'VE BEEN THAT.

00:40:01,900 --> 00:40:03,368
WAIT, WAIT, WAIT, WAIT.

00:40:03,368 --> 00:40:06,237
IS YOUR EX‐HUSBAND
A FRIENDLY EX‐HUSBAND?
YES.

00:40:06,237 --> 00:40:07,906
WILL HE VET THIS

00:40:07,906 --> 00:40:10,575
INTO THE COMPANY
FOR A PIECE OF YOUR EQUITY?
YES.

00:40:10,575 --> 00:40:12,577
NOW WAIT, WAIT, WAIT, WAIT.
CAN YOU‐‐

00:40:12,577 --> 00:40:15,580
JUST SO WE CAN DECIDE WHAT WE'RE
GONNA DO WITH OUR TIME TODAY‐‐

00:40:15,580 --> 00:40:19,450
IS THIS PATENT‐‐IS IT AVAILABLE
TO PUT INTO THE COMPANY?
YES.

00:40:19,450 --> 00:40:22,186
OKAY, ALLISON, JUST TELL ME
YOU'LL THROW THE PATENT

00:40:22,186 --> 00:40:24,555
INTO THE COMPANY.
WE'LL THROW THE PATENT
INTO THE COMPANY.

00:40:24,555 --> 00:40:26,224
(Barbara) OKAY.
OH!

00:40:26,224 --> 00:40:27,992
(Robert) ARE WE‐‐
ARE WE BACK, THEN?

00:40:27,992 --> 00:40:30,028
I DON'T KNOW.
ARE WE BACK ON?

00:40:30,028 --> 00:40:32,997
I LOVE THESE GIRLS. THESE ARE
CRAZY, CRAZY CHICKENS.
(Robert) WELL, HANG ON‐‐

00:40:32,997 --> 00:40:35,800
WAIT. LET'S MODIFY
THIS DEAL A LITTLE BIT.

00:40:35,800 --> 00:40:38,069
LET'S LEAVE IT AT THE $350,000.

00:40:38,069 --> 00:40:41,072
I WANT TO GO A THIRD, A THIRD,
A THIRD WITH DAYMOND.
WHAT'S THE DOLLAR AMOUNT
THAT‐‐THAT'S ON THE TABLE?

00:40:41,072 --> 00:40:43,007
$350,000.
NO. IT WAS UP TO $500,000.

00:40:43,007 --> 00:40:45,476
IT WAS UP
TO $500,00 BEFORE.

00:40:45,476 --> 00:40:47,378
$350,000 CASH.

00:40:47,378 --> 00:40:48,880
YOU GET DAYMOND

00:40:48,880 --> 00:40:52,283
AND THE BACK OFFICE,
WHICH IS AMAZING.

00:40:52,283 --> 00:40:56,020
YOU UNCLE KEVIN AND YOU GET
ROBERT WHEN YOU NEED MORE CASH.

00:40:56,020 --> 00:40:58,022
BUT WE GOTTA START AT 51%.

00:40:58,022 --> 00:41:01,492
WELL, LET ME JUST MAKE
A COUPLE OF COMMENTS HERE.

00:41:01,492 --> 00:41:03,861
ONE, MEN ALWAYS WANT
THE CONTROL.

00:41:03,861 --> 00:41:06,497
THEY'LL PACKAGE IT THIS WAY
OR THAT WAY,

00:41:06,497 --> 00:41:07,999
AND IT MAKES GREAT SENSE,

00:41:07,999 --> 00:41:10,635
BUT IN THE END,
THEY WANT THE CONTROL.

00:41:10,635 --> 00:41:13,304
I, TOO, HAD A MAJORITY PARTNER
AT ONE TIME,

00:41:13,304 --> 00:41:16,074
AND HE ONLY WANTED
1 MORE PERCENT.

00:41:16,074 --> 00:41:18,076
AND SEVEN YEARS LATER,
HE MARRIED MY SECRETARY.

00:41:18,076 --> 00:41:20,812
HE LEFT ME HIGH AND DRY
AND ALMOST BROKE MY BACK.

00:41:20,812 --> 00:41:22,914
SO I'VE BEEN THERE.

00:41:22,914 --> 00:41:25,717
BARBARA, YOU ARE A BLACK WIDOW
IN STILETTOS.

00:41:25,717 --> 00:41:27,852
(Daymond) BARBARA IS GREAT.
(Amy) BARBARA'S FABULOUS.

00:41:27,852 --> 00:41:30,321
I THINK SHE MAKES TOTAL SENSE.
YOU'RE FABULOUS.

00:41:30,321 --> 00:41:32,290
ONE OFFER IS THREE SHARKS,

00:41:32,290 --> 00:41:36,594
$350,000, FOR 51%.

00:41:36,594 --> 00:41:38,763
THE OTHER OFFER
IS ONE SHARK...

00:41:38,763 --> 00:41:40,765
AN HONEST SHARK.
(O'Leary) A SHARKETTE.

00:41:40,765 --> 00:41:43,735
FOR‐‐FOR $350,000 WITH LOTS
OF CONDITIONS ON THE MONEY‐‐

00:41:43,735 --> 00:41:45,336
FOR 40%.
ONE.

00:41:45,336 --> 00:41:48,506
WE HAVE TO MAKE
A DECISION.

00:41:48,506 --> 00:41:52,777
♪♪

00:41:52,777 --> 00:41:55,079
(whispers) WHAT DO YOU
WANT TO DO?

00:41:57,915 --> 00:41:59,417
(whispers)
YOU WANT TO DO IT?

00:41:59,417 --> 00:42:01,285
(normal voice) ALL RIGHT,
BARBARA. YOU'RE IN.

00:42:01,285 --> 00:42:02,887
(O'Leary) LADIES...

00:42:02,887 --> 00:42:04,789
ALL RIGHT. (laughs)
LADIES, LADIES, LADIES.

00:42:04,789 --> 00:42:06,691
(Amy) THANK YOU, GUYS.
LADIES, LADIES, I THINK
YOU MADE A MISTAKE.

00:42:06,691 --> 00:42:09,060
(Daymond)
YOU MADE A BIG MISTAKE.
YOU DID NOT.

00:42:09,060 --> 00:42:11,496
(Robert) HORRIBLE MISTAKE.
(O'Leary)
YOU MADE A HUGE MISTAKE.

00:42:11,496 --> 00:42:14,232
(Allison)
I DON'T THINK WE DID.
YOU KNOW WHAT YOU'RE GONNA DO?
YOU'RE GONNA BE SUCCESSFUL,

00:42:14,232 --> 00:42:17,502
AND YOU'RE GONNA BE HAPPY.
WAIT AND SEE.
(Amy) WE MADE A GREAT DEAL.

00:42:17,502 --> 00:42:19,303
LADIES, IT'S OVER BETWEEN US.

00:42:19,303 --> 00:42:21,039
(Amy laughs) OKAY, GOOD‐BYE.

00:42:21,039 --> 00:42:23,841
OH, MY GOD.
OH, MY GOD.

00:42:23,841 --> 00:42:25,877
YOU GOT 'EM. YOU SH‐‐
YOU OUT‐SHARKED 'EM.

00:42:25,877 --> 00:42:28,846
BARBARA AGAINST
THE THREE OF YOU GUYS?

00:42:28,846 --> 00:42:31,416
HOW DID YOU GUYS LET BARBARA
TAKE DOWN THE THREE OF YOU?

00:42:31,416 --> 00:42:33,785
YOU KNOW WHY?
THEY WERE TOO GREEDY.
(speaks indistinctly)

00:42:33,785 --> 00:42:36,554
WELL DONE, BARBARA.
UNBELIEVABLE.
(Barbara) THANK YOU.

00:42:36,554 --> 00:42:38,022
I CAN'T BELIEVE I'M CRYING.

00:42:38,022 --> 00:42:40,258
YOU KNOW, THE OPPORTUNITY,
IT JUST GAVE US HOPE, YOU KNOW,

00:42:40,258 --> 00:42:42,960
THAT THERE'S SOMEBODY
WILLING TO HELP US.

00:42:42,960 --> 00:42:46,831
AND THEY BELIEVE
THAT OUR PRODUCT IS JUST...

00:42:46,831 --> 00:42:48,833
IT HAS SOMETHING.

